        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 5:25PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 525 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near New Glasgow, or near Clifford, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Amherst...
Bent Creek...
Clifford...
New Canton...
Centenary...
Riverville...
and New Glasgow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
